\begin_layout Proof
Given an endowment, 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

, production labor market clearing in each period requires:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int_{0}^{1}l_{i,t}(w)d(i)=L.
\]

\end_inset

That is,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
L=\int_{0}^{1}\frac{c_{i,t}}{\phi}y_{i,t}\left(w_{t}\right)d(i)=\frac{1}{\phi}\frac{Y_{t}}{w_{t}},
\]

\end_inset

where the second equality comes from using the demand for output of product
 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 for 
